headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 16 of his 25 points in the fourth quarter and the Chicago Bulls pulled away for a 122-112 win against the Detroit Pistons on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zach LaVine's 16 fourth-quarter points lead Bulls past Pistons 122-112

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored a season-high 30 points in his return from a sprained ankle, Tyler Herro added 18 and the Miami Heat erased an early 19-point deficit to beat the Philadelphia 76ers 106-89 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat shake off early deficit, roll past reeling 76ers 106-89

events.name: Washington Wizards at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson had 26 points and 11 assists, and the New York Knicks rolled to a 134-106 victory Monday night that extended the Washington Wizards' losing streak to nine games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson, Towns help Knicks roll to a 134-106 win that extends' Wizards' losing streak to 9

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored a season-high 39 points, Jakob Poeltl had 30 points and 15 rebounds for his third straight double-double and the Toronto Raptors snapped a seven-game losing streak by beating the Indiana Pacers 130-119 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett scores season-high 39 as Raptors snap 7-game losing streak, beat Pacers 130-119

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard hit a driving layup with 3.9 seconds left to give the Milwaukee Bucks a 101-100 victory over Houston that snapped the Rockets’ five-game winning streak Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks win 101-100 on Lillard's late basket to snap Rockets' 5-game win streak

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 32 points, Anthony Black added 20 and the Orlando Magic beat the struggling Phoenix Suns 109-99 Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wagner scores 32 points, Black adds 20 as Magic beat the Suns 109-99

events.name: Golden State Warriors at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Norman Powell scored 23 points and the Los Angeles Clippers held off the Golden State Warriors 102-99 on Monday night to win their fifth in a row at home.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell scores 23 points and the Clippers hold off the Warriors 102-99
